Environmental criteria to classify investment projects

1. Environmental criteria to classify investment projects include:

a) Scale, capacity, type production, business, service;

b) Land use area, land with water surface, sea area; scale of exploitation of natural resources;

c) Environmentally sensitive factors including concentrated residential areas; water sources used for domestic water supply purposes; nature conservation areas according to the provisions of the law on biodiversity and fisheries; types of forests according to the provisions of the law on forestry industrial heritage; tangible cultural heritage, other natural heritage; land for wet rice cultivation with two or more crops; important wetlands; requirements for migration, resettlement and other sensitive environmental factors. 

2. Based on environmental criteria specified in Clause 1 of this Article, investment projects are classified into groups I, II, III and IV.

3. Group I investment projects are projects. having a high risk of adverse impacts on the environment, including:

a) Projects in the form of production, business and services that are likely to cause environmental pollution with large scale and capacity; projects to perform hazardous waste treatment services; projects that import scrap from abroad as raw materials for production;

b) Projects of the type of production, business or service that are likely to cause environmental pollution with an average scale and capacity but have environmental sensitivities; projects that are not of the type of production, business or service that are likely to cause environmental pollution with large scale and capacity but have sensitive environmental factors;

c) Projects using land, land with water surface, sea area with large scale or medium scale but with sensitive environmental factors;

d) Projects to exploit minerals and water resources with large scale and capacity or with medium scale and capacity but with environmental sensitive factors;

đ) The project requires the change of land use purpose of medium scale or more but has environmental sensitive factors ;

e) The project requires large-scale migration and resettlement.

4. Group II investment projects are projects that are likely to have adverse impacts on the environment, except for projects specified in Clause 3 of this Article, including:

a) Projects in the form of production, business and service services with the risk of causing environmental pollution with medium scale and capacity;

b) Projects of the type of production, business or service that are likely to cause environmental pollution with scale and capacity small but sensitive to the environment; projects that are not of the type of production, business or service that are likely to cause environmental pollution with medium scale and capacity but have environmental sensitive factors;

c) Land use projects , land with water surface, marine area with medium scale or small scale but with sensitive environmental factors;

d) Projects to exploit minerals and water resources with scale and capacity medium or with small scale and capacity but with environmentally sensitive factors;

đ) The project requires a small-scale change of land use purpose but has environmental sensitive factors; 

e) The project requires migration and resettlement on a medium scale.

5. Group III investment projects are projects with little risk of adverse impacts on the environment, except for projects specified in Clauses 3 and 4 of this Article, including:

a) Projects of the type of production, business and services that are likely to cause environmental pollution with a small scale and capacity; waste water, dust, and exhaust gas must be treated or hazardous waste generated must be managed according to regulations on waste management.

6. Group IV investment projects are projects with no risk of adverse impacts on the environment, including projects not specified in Clauses 3, 4 and 5 of this Article.

7. The Government shall detail Clause 1 and promulgate a list of types of investment projects specified in Clauses 3, 4 and 5 of this Article.

