c) Scientific and technological activities specified at Points a and Points a and b. b Clause 2, Article 6 of this Law;

d) Training human resources on agricultural extension for regions with difficult or extremely difficult socio-economic conditions.

2. In each period and With the state budget's capacity, the State supports the following activities:

a) Linking production, forming concentrated commodity production areas, organic farming; transforming tree structure planting; cultivating on sloping land, low-lying land, alkaline soil, saline soil, coastal sandy soil, land at risk of desertification or desertification; developing raw material areas for processing factories; management of growing areas and traceability;

b) Scientific and technological activities specified at Point c, Clause 2, Article 6 of this Law;

c) Application of an advanced quality management system , plant product certification activities;

d) Building infrastructure, analyzing and assessing initial production conditions in crop production, assessing agrochemicals and soils for commodity production concentrate; building infrastructure in service of preservation and processing; production of organic fertilizers and biological products; organic farming; machine-based; national testing laboratory and international interlaboratory testing;

đ) Production of rice as planned;

e) Producing super-primary seeds, original varieties, and parent varieties to produce F1 hybrid seeds , original varieties and new commercial varieties; restore specialty plant varieties and indigenous plant varieties; maintain the bullet tree; protect and develop top-notch orchards; import of new varieties, transfer of copyright for plant varieties;

g) Building a wholesale market for plant products; building brands, promoting trade, developing markets for crop products;

h) Restoring production in case of natural disasters and epidemics;

i) Training human resources ; transfer of scientific and technical advances, agricultural extension in crop production.

