Scientific and technological activities in crop cultivation

1. Scientific and technological activities in crop production shall comply with the provisions of this Law, the law on science and technology, transfer technology transfer.

2. Scientific and technological activities in crop production that are invested or supported by the State include:

a) Research on mechanisms and policies in crop production; select, creating high-quality plant varieties, resistant to harmful organisms and adapting to climate change; exploiting beneficial organisms; developing organic fertilizers, biological products, farming techniques and protecting the environment field in cultivation; research on soil science and plant nutrition, post-harvest technology;

b) Collect, store, conserve and exploit genetic resources of precious and rare plant varieties and plant varieties specialties, indigenous plant varieties; construction of plant gene banks;

c) Research, development and application of high technology, advanced technology, new technology in cultivation, preservation and processing ; organic farming, farming that adapts to climate change.

Luật Trồng trọt@7:
International cooperation on crop production

1. The State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam implements international cooperation in crop production with other countries, territories and international organizations in the world. on the basis of equality, mutual benefit, respect for the independence, sovereignty, law of each party and international law.

2. Priority content for international cooperation on crop production includes:

a) Scientific research, technology transfer on plant varieties, agricultural materials, production process and technology, post-harvest technology, exchange of information and plant genetic resources;

b) Training high-quality human resources in crop production;

c) Cooperation in investment, production linkages, forecasting and market development for crop products;

d) Construction and surplus mutual recognition of the quality certification system in crop production.

3. The Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with ministries, ministerial-level agencies, and provincial-level People's Committees in implementing cooperation. International Horticulture.

Luật Trồng trọt@8:
National database on cultivation

1. National database on cultivation is an information system related to cultivation, built uniformly from central to local levels. . legal regulations, executive directive documents related to cultivation;

b) Database of production, preservation, processing and trade on cultivation;

c) Database on the results of scientific research and technological development, standards and technical regulations; data on soil nutrition, cropland use; data on plant varieties, fertilizers, irrigation water; ) Other databases on cultivation.

3. Organizations and individuals providing information, updating and exploiting the national database on cultivation in accordance with law.

4 The Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development shall prescribe the provision of information, updating, exploiting and managing the national database on crop production.

Luật Trồng trọt@12:
Conservation of genetic resources of plant varieties

1. Conservation of genetic resources of plant varieties includes the following activities:

a) Investigating, collecting, storing and building a bank plant variety genes;

b) Decoding genes, assessing agronomical and biological criteria and the value of using genetic resources of plant varieties;

c) Establishing and sharing data, information systems information on documents and genetic resources of plant varieties.

2. The Government shall detail the conservation of genetic resources of plant varieties and promulgate the List of genetic resources of plant varieties banned from export.

Luật Trồng trọt@14:
Variety name

1. Variety name is not accepted in the following cases:

a) Include only numbers;

b) Violation of historical tradition , culture, morality and fine customs of the nation;

c) The same reading or writing with the names of leaders, national heroes, celebrities, foods, beverages, pharmaceuticals ;

d) Using names of state agencies, people's armed forces units, political organizations, socio-political organizations, socio-political-professional organizations, social organizations, and organizations a social-professional organization to make all or part of the proper name of the plant variety, unless it is approved by the relevant agency, organization or unit;

đ) Easily misleading about characteristics, characteristics of that variety;

e) It is easy to mislead the identity of the author;

g) It matches the name of a protected plant variety.

2. Organization, individuals buying and selling propagating materials of plant varieties must use the name of the variety which has been granted the Decision on recognition of circulation of the plant variety or self-declares the circulation of the plant variety.

3. When using the name of a plant variety in combination with a trademark, trade name or indications similar to the name of a plant variety that has been recognized for circulation or announced for circulation for production or sale, such name must be capable of easily recognizable.

Luật Trồng trọt@15:
Issuing, re-granting, extending, suspending, reinstating, canceling the Decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties

1. Conditions for granting the Decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties include: 

a) Having the name of the plant variety;

b) Having test results ensuring the distinctiveness, uniformity, stability;

c) Having test results meeting national standards about cultivation value and use value;

d) Having a plant variety sample stored as prescribed in Article 20 of this Law;

đ) Having a publication of information on plant variety, regulations The production process is compiled by the organization or individual that is registered for the grant of the Decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties.

2. The annual decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties has a term of 10 years. Perennial plants have a term of 20 years and can be extended.

3. The decision on recognition of circulation of the plant variety shall be re-issued in the following cases:

a) The decision on recognition of circulation of the plant variety shall be re-issued in the following cases:

a) plants are lost or damaged;

b) Change, supplement information related to the Decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties.

4. A decision on recognition of circulation of a plant variety may be extended when the following conditions are met:

a) Upon request by an organization or individual;

b) There are results of controlled testing as prescribed in Clause 2 of this Article. Point a, Clause 2, Article 18 of this Law meets the national standards of value for cultivation and use.

5. The decision on recognition of circulation of a plant variety is suspended when the plant variety fails to maintain the uniformity or stability or the value of cultivation or use as at the time of issuance of the decision on circulation of the plant variety. plant.

6. The decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties that has been suspended shall be reinstated when the organization or individual issued with the Decision on recognition of circulation of the plant variety overcomes the cases specified in Clause 5 of this Article.

7. The decision on recognition of circulation of a plant variety is annulled in the following cases:

a) Fraud in the application for registration for recognition of circulation of a plant variety;

b) The distinctiveness of the plant variety cannot be maintained; plant varieties as at the time of issuance of the Decision on recognition of circulation of plant varieties;

c) The case specified in Clause 5 of this Article cannot be remedied;

d) The administrative violation has been sanctioned about plant varieties but still commits the offence;

đ) There are other violations that must be abolished by law.

8. The Government shall stipulate dossiers, order, procedures and competence for granting, re-granting, extending, suspending, reinstating or canceling decisions on recognition of circulation of plant varieties.

Luật Trồng trọt@18:
Content of plant variety testing

1. Testing for distinctness, uniformity and stability of plant varieties.

2. Cultivation value and use value testing Uses of plant varieties include:

a) Controlled trials;

b) Small field trials;

c) Large field trials.

