Luật Trồng trọt@30:
Rights and obligations of organizations and individuals researching, selecting and creating plant varieties

1. Organizations and individuals researching, selecting and creating plant varieties have the following rights:

a) Investing in research, selection and breeding of plant varieties; investigating, evaluating, collecting, storing and exploiting domestic or imported sources of propagation materials in service of research, selection and breeding of plant varieties. ;

b) Enjoy the State's support policies on investment in science and technology, specific policies for fields and regions as prescribed by law;

c) Cooperate with organizations domestic and foreign organizations and individuals to research, select and create plant varieties according to the provisions of law.

2. Organizations and individuals researching, selecting and creating plant varieties have the following obligations :

a) To fulfill all obligations as prescribed by the law on science and technology, and other relevant laws;

b) Register for protection of rights to plant varieties before putting them into business or transferring them in the case of research, selection, creation, discovery and development of plant varieties with the state budget or from projects managed by the State; when transferring plant varieties, they must comply with the provisions of the law on technology transfer;

c) Comply with the provisions of the law on biodiversity and other relevant laws when conducting the transfer of plant varieties. conducting research, selection, creation, experimentation and testing of genetically modified plant varieties.

Luật Trồng trọt@32:
Rights and obligations of organizations and individuals using plant varieties

1. Organizations and individuals using plant varieties have the following rights:

