Luật Trồng trọt@37:
Issuing, re-granting and extending the Decision on recognition of fertilizers circulating in Vietnam

1. Conditions for granting the Decision on recognition of fertilizers circulating in Vietnam include:

a) Satisfying the quality criteria according to the national technical regulations on fertilizer quality;

b) Having test results meeting national standards, except for fertilizers specified in Clause 2, Article 39 of this Law .

2. A decision on recognition of fertilizers in circulation in Vietnam may be re-issued in the following cases:

a) Changes or additions of information related to organizations and individuals in the Public Decision receive fertilizers in circulation;

b) Decision on recognition of fertilizers in circulation lost or damaged;

c) Change the name of fertilizers under decisions of competent state management agencies or according to regulations. Court judgments and decisions in case of violations of the law on intellectual property.

3. Decisions on recognition of fertilizers circulating in Vietnam may be extended when the following conditions are met:

a) At the request of an organization or individual;

b) Meeting the quality criteria according to the national technical regulation on fertilizer quality;

c) Report on production and export import, import and use fertilizers according to regulations.

4. The Government shall stipulate dossiers, order, procedures and competence for granting, re-granting and extending decisions on recognition of fertilizers circulating in Vietnam.

Luật Trồng trọt@39:
Requirement for fertilizer testing

1. Fertilizers must be tested before being recognized for circulation, except for fertilizers specified in Clause 2 of this Article.

2. fertilizers that are not subject to testing include:

a) Organic fertilizers used to fertilize roots have only natural organic ingredients and meet quality criteria according to national technical regulations;

b) Single inorganic fertilizer used to fertilize roots with ingredients containing only nitrogen (N) or phosphorus (P) or potassium (K), meeting the quality criteria according to national technical regulations;

c) Complex inorganic fertilizers used to fertilize roots in ingredients containing only the nutritional elements nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), potassium (K) linked together by chemical bonds, meet quality criteria according to national technical regulations;

d) Fertilizers are recognized as technical progress by competent state management agencies.

3. Fertilizers are tested both large-scale and narrow-scale trials; large-scale trials are conducted only after the narrow-scale trials are completed.

4. Fertilizer testing is carried out according to national standards set by an accredited organization qualified to conduct testing.

5. The amount of fertilizer produced and imported for testing is determined based on the fertilizer dose for each crop and the actual testing area according to the national standards for fertilizer testing.

Luật Trồng trọt@40:
Conditions for recognition of a fertilizer testing organization

1. A fertilizer testing organization must ensure the following conditions:

a) Persons directly in charge of testing must have a University degree or higher in one of the majors in horticulture, plant protection, agrochemistry, soil science, soil science, agronomy, chemistry, biology, and must participate in fertilizer testing training in the direction of: instructions of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development;

b) Having a sufficient number of human resources to conduct the testing, excluding those directly in charge of testing, with university or higher degrees in one of the specialties. branches specified at Point a, Clause 1 of this Article and must participate in training in fertilizer testing under the guidance of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development;

c) Having adequate facilities and equipment according to regulations. national standards on fertilizer testing.

2. The Government shall stipulate the minimum number of human resources to perform the testing of the fertilizer testing organization; dossiers, order, procedures and competence for granting, revoke the decision on recognition of the fertilizer testing organization.

Luật Trồng trọt@41:
Conditions for fertilizer production

1. Fertilizer-producing organizations and individuals must have a Certificate of eligibility for fertilizer production.

2. Conditions for issuance of a Certificate of eligibility. Conditions for fertilizer production include:

a) Having a production location and workshop area suitable to the production scale;

b) Having production lines, machinery and equipment suitable to regulations production process of each type and form of fertilizer;

c) Having a testing laboratory or having a contract with a designated testing organization to evaluate the quality criteria of fertilizers produced by them;

d ) Having an appropriate and updated quality management system with standards issued by the international standardization organization on quality management;

đ) Having separate areas for storing raw materials and finished products. special;

e) The person directly managing the production must have a university degree or higher in one of the majors in cultivation, plant protection, agrochemistry, soil science, soil science, agronomy, chemical, biological.

3. The certificate of eligibility for fertilizer production is valid for 5 years and is re-issued.

4. The Government shall detail the conditions, dossiers, order, procedures and competence for granting, re-granting and revoking the Certificate of eligibility for fertilizer production.

Luật Trồng trọt@44:
Importing fertilizers

1. Organizations and individuals with fertilizers that have been granted the Decision on recognition of fertilizers in circulation in Vietnam may import or authorize the import of fertilizers in the Decision No. receive fertilizers in circulation in Vietnam and do not need a fertilizer import license.

2. Organizations and individuals importing fertilizers that have not been recognized for circulation in Vietnam must have a fertilizer import license within the following cases:

a) Fertilizers for testing;

b) Fertilizers used for sports fields, amusement parks;

c) Fertilizers used in foreign projects in Vietnam;

d) Fertilizers as gifts, samples;

đ) Fertilizers for fairs and exhibitions;

e) Fertilizers for scientific research;

g) Fertilizers used as raw materials for the production of other fertilizers;

h) Fertilizers temporarily imported for re-export or in transit or transferred through Vietnam's border gates; fertilizers stored in bonded warehouses; fertilizers import into export processing zones.

3. The Government shall prescribe dossiers, order, procedures and competence to grant fertilizer import permits.

Luật Trồng trọt@48:
Fertilizer labeling

