a) Recognized fertilizer production circulated in Vietnam;

b) Producing fertilizers for export under contracts with foreign organizations and individuals;

c) Advertising fertilizers as prescribed in Article 49 of this Law;

d) To trade in fertilizers they produce.

2. Fertilizer-producing organizations and individuals have the following obligations:

a) To fully maintain fertilizer production conditions specified in Article 41 of this Law in the course of fertilizer production;

b) Producing fertilizer in accordance with national technical regulations and announced applicable standards;

c) Properly content of the Certificate of eligibility for fertilizer production;

d) Testing for each batch of finished fertilizer before being put on the market. fertilizers and samples stored for a period of 6 months from the date of sampling;

đ) Recover and treat fertilizers that do not meet quality standards and compensate for damage in accordance with the law;

e) Comply with the inspection and examination of the competent state agencies;

g) Organize training and guidance on fertilizer use; provide training and professional training for employees directly producing fertilizers;

h) Annually, report the situation of fertilizer production, export and import to competent state management agencies. or make irregular reports upon request;

i) Comply with the provisions of the law on fire prevention and fighting, chemicals, labor, environment and other relevant laws.

Luật Trồng trọt@51:
Rights and obligations of organizations and individuals trading in fertilizers

1. Organizations and individuals trading in fertilizers have the following rights:

a) Trade in fertilizers is recognized. to be circulated in Vietnam;

b) To be provided with information and guidance on fertilizer use and professional training.

2. Organizations and individuals trading in fertilizers have the following obligations: n
a) To fully maintain the fertilizer trading conditions specified in Article 42 of this Law during the fertilizer trading process;

b) Store fertilizers in a dry place, not to be mixed with other fertilizers. other goods that affect fertilizer quality;

c) Check fertilizer origin, fertilizer label, standard conformity mark, regulation conformity mark and other documents related to fertilizer quality; 
d) Comply with the inspection and examination of the competent state agencies;

đ) Provide legal documents to trace the origin of fertilizers;

e) Compensation for damage according to regulations provisions of the law;

g) Instructions on the use of fertilizers in accordance with the content stated on the fertilizer label;

h) Comply with the provisions of the law on fire prevention and fighting, chemicals, labor , environment and other provisions of relevant laws.

