a) To use fertilizers strictly according to the instructions on the label;

b) To use fertilizers that are effective fruit, safe for people, livestock, environment, food safety according to the principle of right soil type, right type of tree, right dose, right time, right way.

3. Ministry of Agriculture and Development rural areas to develop and disseminate a set of documents guiding the use of fertilizers according to the provisions of Point b, Clause 2 of this Article.

Luật Trồng trọt@56:
Transformation of crop structure on rice land

1. The transformation of crop structure on rice land is regulated as follows:

a) In accordance with land use planning local production, market demand, water source conditions and climate;

b) Forming concentrated production areas according to each crop associated with consolidation, change of plots, and chain production;

c) Ensure efficient exploitation of the available infrastructure; conform to the planning and orientation to complete the infrastructure for agricultural production in the locality;

d) Do not lose the necessary conditions for rice cultivation to resume.

2. The Government shall detail this Article.

Luật Trồng trọt@60:
Agricultural equipment and supplies in farming

1. Farming equipment includes greenhouses, net houses, machines and tools for production, irrigation and harvesting. , preliminary processing, preservation, processing.

2. Agricultural materials in cultivation include:

a) Plant varieties;

b) Fertilizers;

c) Pesticides plants;

d) Planting media, soil mulch, moisture-retaining materials;

đ) Chemicals and biological products used in farming activities other than the materials specified at point b and point c of this clause.

3. The management of the quality of agricultural equipment and supplies in farming is carried out in accordance with the law on standards and technical regulations, quality, and products. goods.

Luật Trồng trọt@66:
Application of high technology in farming

1. High technology that is prioritized and encouraged for application in farming includes:

a) Biotechnology in genetic selection, generation plant varieties; diagnosis and assessment of plant pests; development of biological products and new materials;

b) Water-saving irrigation technology, cultivation without soil;

c) Production technology in greenhouse and greenhouse conditions;

d) Information technology applied in forecasting and forecasting harmful organisms; issuing codes and managing growing areas;

 d) Precision agricultural techniques applied in soil science and plant nutrition; automatic control of fertilizer and irrigation water regimes; semi-automatic and automatic technology in production lines; quality analysis production environment and quality of crop products.

2. Priority is to be given to the application of high technologies specified at Points b and c, Clause 1 of this Article in difficult cultivation areas, coastal sandy soils, and soils with poor quality. the risk of desertification and desertification.

3. The high technology specified at point c, clause 1 of this Article is built with appropriate density, reducing greenhouse gas effects.

Luật Trồng trọt@72:
Protecting the environment in farming

1. Farming organizations and individuals must ensure the following requirements:

a) Comply with the law on environmental protection and other regulations of relevant laws;

b) Comply with the guidance of specialized agencies when using agricultural materials in farming with the risk of causing environmental pollution;

c) Collect, treat , using plant by-products as prescribed in Article 76 of this Law.

2. Organizations and individuals shall promptly notify commune-level People's Committees when detecting abnormal signs of environmental pollution. potentially affecting farming activities.

Luật Trồng trọt@82:
Responsibility of the Government, Ministries, and ministerial-level agencies

1. The Government performs the unified state management of farming activities nationwide.

2. The Ministry of Agriculture and Rural development is the focal agency to help the Government perform the state management of crop production nationwide and has the following responsibilities:

a) Formulating strategies, schemes and plans ; directing and guiding the implementation of cultivation activities;

b) Promulgating according to their competence or submitting to competent authorities for promulgation and organizing the implementation of policies, legal documents, standards and regulations techniques and production processes in farming activities;

c) Organizing the grant, re-grant, extension, suspension, reinstatement, revocation, cancellation of decisions, permits and certificates in cultivation activities according to its competence and posted on the Ministry's web portal;

d) Building a database and information system; making statistics and reports on cultivation activities ;

đ) Organizing research and application of science and technology; basic investigation, collection and management of information, documents and international cooperation in farming activities;

e) Training and fostering professional knowledge; propagating, disseminating and educating the law on cultivation activities;

g) Inspect, examine, settle complaints and denunciations, handle violations of the law in cultivation activities.

3. Ministries and ministerial-level agencies shall, within the ambit of their tasks and powers, have to coordinate with the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development in performing the task of state management of crop production activities.

Luật Trồng trọt@83:
