Luật Tố tụng hành chính@361:
Obligation to pay assessment expense advance

Unless otherwise agreed upon by the involved parties or not otherwise provided by law, the obligation to pay the expertising expense advance shall be determined. as follows:

1. The person requesting the Court to solicit expertise must pay an expertising expense advance.

In case the involved parties request the Court to solicit expertise on the same object, each the involved party must pay half of the expertising expense advance;

2. In case the Court considers it necessary and decides to solicit expertise, the plaintiff or the appellant according to appellate procedures must pay an expertising expense advance;

3. The involved parties and appellants have requested the Court to solicit expertise but are not accepted and request the organization or individual to conduct the expertise by themselves, the payment of expertising expense advances shall comply with the provisions of the Law on judicial expertise.

Luật Tố tụng hành chính@362:
Obligation to bear expertising expenses

Unless the involved parties agree otherwise or the law does not provide otherwise, the obligation to bear expertise costs is determined as follows:

1. The person who requests the Court to solicit expertise must bear the expertising costs, if the expertise results prove that such person's claim is groundless. if there is a partial basis, they must pay the cost of expertise for the part of their claim that has been proven to be groundless;

2. Those who do not accept the request for expertise solicitation of other involved parties in the the case must pay expertising costs, if the expertise results prove that the expert solicitation request is grounded. the person who does not accept the request for solicitation of expertise shall bear the expertising expenses corresponding to the part of the request which has been proven to be grounded; Point c, Clause 1, Article 143, Clause 1, Article 234 of this Law, the plaintiffs must bear the expertise costs.

In case of suspension of the appellate trial under the provisions of Point a, Clause 2, Article 225, Point c, Clause 1, Article 229 of this Law, the person who appeals according to appellate procedures must bear the expert examination expenses;

4. In case a person personally requests expertise as prescribed in Clause 3, Article 361 of this Law, if the assessment results prove that his/her request is grounded, the loser of the lawsuit must bear the expertise costs. If the assessment results prove that their request for expertise is only partially grounded, they must pay the cost of expertise for the part of their claim that has been proven to be groundless;

5. For other cases of termination of the settlement of the case under the provisions of this Law, the person requesting expertise solicitation shall bear the expert examination expense.

Luật Tố tụng hành chính@365:
Obligation to pay advance payment of asset valuation expenses

Unless the involved parties otherwise agree or otherwise provided by law, the obligation to bear asset valuation expenses shall be determined. determined as follows:

1. The property valuation requester must pay an advance on asset valuation expenses;

2. In case the involved parties cannot agree on the price and jointly request the Court If there are many involved parties, each involved party must pay one half of the asset valuation expense advance. The court shall decide;

3. In the case specified in Clause 3, Article 91 of this Law, the plaintiff or the appellant must pay an advance on asset valuation expenses.

