Bộ luật dân sự@132:
The statute of limitations for requesting the Court to declare a civil transaction invalid

1. The statute of limitations for requesting the Court to declare a civil transaction invalid is specified in Articles 125, 126, 127, 128 and 129 of this Code is 02 years, from date:

a) Representative of minors, persons who have lost their civil act capacity, people with difficulties in cognition, behavior control, a person with limited civil act capacity knows or must know the person represented to establish and perform transactions by himself;

b) The person who is mistaken or deceived knows or must know the established transaction due to confusion, due to deception;

c) Person who threatens or coerces to stop threatening or coercive act;

d) Person who is not aware of and has no control over their behavior you establish a transaction;

đ) A civil transaction is established in case the civil transaction does not comply with the regulations on form.

2. The statute of limitations specified in Clause 1 of this Article has expired. If there is no request to declare a civil transaction invalid, the civil transaction will take effect.

3. For a civil transaction specified in Articles 123 and 124 of this Code, the statute of limitations for requesting the Court is the statute of limitations. judgments declaring civil transactions null and void without restriction.

Bộ luật dân sự@137:
The legal representative of the legal person

1. The legal representative of the legal person includes:

a) The person appointed by the legal person according to the charter;

b) Person authorized by law to represent;

c) Person appointed by the Court in the course of court proceedings.

2. A legal person may have more than one legal representative law and each representative has the right to represent the legal person as prescribed in Articles 140 and 141 of this Code.

Bộ luật dân sự@140:
Term of representation

1. The term of representation is determined by a written authorization, by a decision of a competent authority, by a charter of a legal entity or by law. .

2. In case the term of representation cannot be determined as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article, the term of representation shall be determined as follows:

a) If the representation is determined according to the transaction For a specific civil transaction, the term of representation shall be counted to the time of termination of that civil transaction;

b) If the right of representation is not determined with a specific civil transaction, the term of representation is 1 year . 

c) The authorized work has been completed;

d) The principal or the representative unilaterally terminates the authorization;

đ) The principal, the representative being an individual dies; the represented person, the representative being a legal entity ceases to exist;

e) The representative no longer satisfies the conditions specified in Clause 3, Article 134 of this Code;

g ) Other grounds make the representation impossible.

4. The legal representation terminates in the following cases:

a) The represented person is an adult individual or the civil act capacity has been restored;

b) The represented person is the individual dies;

c) The person represented as a legal entity ceases to exist;

d) Other grounds as prescribed by this Code or other relevant laws.

Bộ luật dân sự@141:
Scope of representation

1. A representative may only establish and perform civil transactions within the scope of representation on the following grounds:

a) Decision of competent authority authority;

b) Charter of the legal entity;

c) Contents of authorization;

d) Other provisions of law.

2. In case the specific offense cannot be identified vi of representation as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article, the legal representative has the right to establish and perform all civil transactions for the benefit of the represented person, unless otherwise provided for by law.

3. An individual or legal entity may represent many different individuals or legal entities, but may not act on behalf of the represented person to establish and perform civil transactions with himself or with a third party. in which he is also his representative, unless otherwise provided for by law.

4. The representative must notify the transaction party of the scope of his/her representation.

Bộ luật dân sự@146:
Stipulation on the time limit and time to calculate the time limit

1. In case the parties agree on the term of one year, half a year, one month, half a month, one week, one day, an hour, a minute but the time period is not consecutive, that time period is calculated as follows:

a) A year is three hundred and sixty-five days;

b) Half a year is six months;

c) A month is thirty days;

d) Half a month is fifteen days;

đ) A week is seven days;

e) A day is twenty-four hours;

g) One hour is sixty minutes;

h) One minute is sixty seconds.

2. Where the parties agree on the beginning of the month, the middle of the month, the end of the month, such time shall be specified. as follows:

a) The beginning of the month is the first day of the month;

b) The middle of the month is the fifteenth day of the month;

c) The end of the month is the last day of the month.

3 Where the parties agree on the beginning of the year, the middle of the year, the end of the year, that time is specified as follows:

a) The beginning of the year is the first day of January;

b) The middle of the year is the last day of June;

c) Year-end is the last day of December.

Bộ luật dân sự@155:
The statute of limitations does not apply

The statute of limitations for initiating a lawsuit does not apply in the following cases:

1. The requirement to protect moral rights is not tied to property;

2 Request for protection of ownership rights, unless otherwise provided for by this Code or other relevant laws;

3. Disputes over land use rights in accordance with the Land Law;

4. Other cases prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@156:
Time does not include the statute of limitations for initiating a civil case, the statute of limitations for requesting the resolution of a civil matter

Time is not included in the statute of limitations for initiating a civil lawsuit, or the statute of limitations for requesting settlement. settlement of a civil matter is the time period when one of the following events occurs:

1. Force majeure events or objective obstacles make the subject of the right to sue or claim unable to initiate a lawsuit, required within the statute of limitations.

A force majeure event is an event that occurs objectively, which cannot be foreseen and cannot be remedied, despite all necessary measures and possibilities for permission.

Objective obstacles are obstacles caused by objective circumstances that make it impossible for persons with civil rights and obligations to know that their legitimate rights and interests have been infringed or cannot be performed. present their civil rights and obligations;

2. There is no representative in case the person with the right to initiate a lawsuit or the person with the right to claim is a minor, has lost his/her civil act capacity, has difficulties in cognition, behavior control or limited capacity for civil acts;

3. A minor, a person who has lost his/her civil act capacity, a person with difficulties in perception or behavior control, or a person with restricted civil act capacity who has not yet been replaced by another representative in the following cases: :

a) The representative dies if he is an individual, ceases to exist if he is a legal entity;

b) The representative cannot continue to represent for a good reason.

Bộ luật dân sự@159:
Other property rights

1. Other property rights are the right of the subject to directly hold and control the property under the ownership of another subject.

2. Other rights to property include:

a) Right to adjoining immovable property;

b) Tenancy right;

c) Surface right.

Bộ luật dân sự@165:
Legal possession

1. Legally grounded possession is the possession of property in the following cases:

a) The owner takes possession of the property;

b) The person authorized by the owner to manage the property;

c) The person who is transferred the right of possession through a civil transaction in accordance with the law;

d) The issuer Realize and keep derelict property, property whose owner is unknown, property that has been dropped, forgotten, buried, hidden, buried, or sunk in accordance with the conditions prescribed by law. This Code and other relevant laws; other relevant provisions of law;

e) Other cases prescribed by law.

2. Possession of property not in accordance with the provisions of Clause 1 of this Article is possession without legal basis.

Bộ luật dân sự@220:
Termination of joint ownership

Common ownership terminates in the following cases:

1. The joint property has been divided;

2. One of the joint owners is enjoy the entire common property;

3. The common property no longer exists;

4. Other cases as prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@221:
Base for establishment of ownership

Ownership is established for property in the following cases:

1. Due to labor, legal production and business activities , due to the creation of intellectual property rights objects;

2. Ownership rights are transferred under an agreement or under a judgment or decision of a court or other competent state agency;

3. Gaining yields and profits;

4. Forming new assets through merger, mixing, processing;

5. Inherited;

6. Possession under conditions as prescribed by law for derelict property, property whose owner cannot be identified; property that is buried, hidden, buried or sunk found; property dropped or forgotten by others; Lost livestock and poultry, aquatic animals that move naturally;

7. Possession of, and benefit from, property as prescribed in Article 236 of this Code;

8. Other cases prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@225:
Establishment of ownership in the event of a merger

1. In case the assets of many different owners are merged together to form an indivisible object and the property to be brought cannot be identified If the merged property is the main or auxiliary object, the newly created object shall be the property under common ownership of those owners; if the merged property is the main object and auxiliary object, the newly created object shall belong to the owner. From the time the new object is created, the owner of the new property must pay the owner of the auxiliary object the value of that auxiliary object, unless otherwise agreed.

2. When a person who incorporates another person's movable property into his own movable property, even though he knew or ought to have known that such property was not his own and without the consent of the owner of the destroyed property. merger, the owner of the property being merged has one of the following rights:

a) To request the person merging the property to hand over the new property to him/her and pay the merged person the value of the property of the merged property. that;

b) Requesting the merger of the property to pay the value of his or her part of the property and compensate for the damage if he does not receive the new property;

c) Other rights as prescribed by law.

3. When a person merges another person's movable property into his or her own immovable property, even though he knew or ought to have known that the property was not his/her own and without the consent of the property owner. If the property is merged, the owner of the merged property has one of the following rights:

a) To request the person merging the property to pay the value of his/her part of the property and pay compensation for damage;

b) Other rights as prescribed by law.

4. When a person merges his or her movable property into another's real estate, the real estate owner has the right to demand that the merger remove the illegally merged property and compensate for the damage or keep it. assets and pay to the merger the value of the merged property, unless otherwise agreed.

Bộ luật dân sự@237:
Base for termination of ownership

Ownership ends in the following cases:

1. Owner transfers his/her ownership rights to another person;

2. Owner owner waives his title;

3. Property has been consumed or destroyed;

4. Property is disposed of to fulfill the owner's obligations;

5 . Property being expropriated;

6. Confiscated property;

7. Property that has been established as ownership for another person in accordance with the provisions of this Code;

8. Cases otherwise prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@248:
Principles for exercising rights to adjoining immovable property
The exercise of rights to adjoining immovable property shall be as agreed upon by the parties. following rules:

1. Ensure that the reasonable needs of the exploitation of the entitled immovable property are suitable for the use purposes of both the entitled immovable and the entitled;

2 . Not to abuse the right to the entitled immovable property;

3. Not to perform acts that prevent or make it difficult for the exercise of the right to the entitled immovable property.

Bộ luật dân sự@256:
Termination of right to adjoining immovable property

Right to adjoining immovable property terminates in the following cases:

1. Entitlement immovable and beneficiary immovable the right belongs to one person;

2. The use and exploitation of real estate no longer gives rise to the need to enjoy the right;

3. According to the agreement of the parties;

4. Other cases as prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@265:
Termination of the usufruct right

The usufruct right shall terminate in the following cases:

1. The term of usufruct has expired;

2. As agreed by the parties; 

3. The usufructee becomes the owner of the property subject to the usufruct right;

4. The usufructee waives or fails to exercise the usufruct right within the time limit prescribed by law;

5. Property subject to usufruct no longer exists;

6. According to court decision;

7. Other grounds as prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@272:
Termination of surface rights

Surface rights terminate in the following cases:

1. Term of surface rights has expired;

2. Surface rights holder and the owner of the land use right is one;

3. The holder of the surface right renounces his or her rights;

4. The land use right with the surface right is revoked according to the provisions of the Land Law ;

5. As agreed by the parties or as prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@275:
The basis for the arising of the obligation

The obligation arises from the following grounds:

1. Contract;

2. Unilateral legal action;

3. Performance perform work without authorization;

4. Possession, use of property or gain from property without a legal basis;

5. Causing damage due to illegal acts;

6. Other grounds prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@292:
Security for performance of obligations

Security for performance of obligations includes:

1. Pledge of property;

2. Mortgage of property;

3. Deposit;

4. Deposit;

5. Deposit;

6. Ownership reservation;

7. Guarantee;

8. Unsecured;

9. Possession of property.

Bộ luật dân sự@303:
Method of handling the pledged or mortgaged property

1. The securing party and the secured party have the right to agree on one of the following methods of handling the pledged or mortgaged property: 

a) Auction of assets;

b) The secured party sells the property itself;

c) The secured party receives the property itself to replace the performance of obligations of the guarantor security;

d) Other methods.

2. If there is no agreement on the method of handling the security property as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article, the property shall be auctioned, unless The law provides otherwise.

Bộ luật dân sự@315:
Termination of pledge of property

Pledge of property terminates in the following cases:

1. Obligations secured by pledge terminates;

2. The pledge the property is canceled or replaced with another security measure;

3. The pledged property has been disposed of;

4. As agreed by the parties.

Bộ luật dân sự@324:
Rights and obligations of the third party holding the mortgaged property

1. The third party holding the mortgaged property has the following rights:

a) To exploit the use of the mortgaged property mortgage, if so agreed;

b) To be paid remuneration and expenses for preservation and maintenance of the mortgaged property, unless otherwise agreed.

2. The third person keeps the mortgaged property. have the following obligations: 

a) To preserve and preserve the mortgaged property; if the mortgaged property is lost, devalued or reduced in value, it must pay compensation;

b) Not to continue exploiting the use of the mortgaged property if the continued exploitation threatens to devalue or reduce the value of the mortgaged property;

c) Hand over the mortgaged property mortgaged to the mortgagee or mortgagor as agreed or prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@327:
Termination of the mortgage of the property

The mortgage of the property shall terminate in the following cases:

1. The obligation secured by the mortgage terminates;

2. The mortgage the property is canceled or replaced with another security measure;

3. The mortgaged property has been disposed of;

4. As agreed by the parties.

Subsection 4

Deposit, ESCROW, ESCROW

Bộ luật dân sự@343:
Termination of the guarantee

The guarantee is terminated in the following cases:

1. The obligation to be guaranteed is terminated;

2. The guarantee is canceled or replaced by other security measures;

3. The guarantor has performed the guarantee obligation;

4. As agreed by the parties.

Subsection 7

ACCEPTED

Bộ luật dân sự@350:
Termination of lien

A lien terminates in the following cases:

1. The lien is no longer physically occupied by the property;

2. The parties agree agree to use other security measures to replace the lien;

3. The obligation has been fulfilled;

4. The lien property is no longer available;

5. As agreed by the parties beside.

Bộ luật dân sự@372:
The ground for termination of the obligation

The obligation to terminate in the following cases:

1. The obligation is fulfilled;

2. As agreed by the parties;

3. The obligee waives the performance of the obligation;

4. The obligation is replaced by another;

5. The obligation is set off;

6. The obligee and the obligee the obligation to integrate into one;

7. The statute of limitations for discharge of obligations has expired;

8. The obligor being an individual dies or the legal entity ceases to exist but the obligation must be due to the individual, the juridical person does;

9. The obligee is an individual who dies but the right to claim does not belong to the inheritance or is a juridical person ceases to exist but the right to claim is not transferred to another juridical person;

10. The specific object that is the subject of the obligation no longer exists and is replaced by another obligation;

11. Other cases prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@379:
Cases in which the obligation is not cleared

The obligation is not cleared in the following cases:

1. The obligation is in dispute;

2. The obligation to indemnify damage caused by infringing upon life, health, honor, dignity and reputation;

3. Support obligations;

4. Other obligations prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@388:
The effective time of the offer to enter into a contract

1. The effective time of the offer to enter into a contract is determined as follows:

a) To be fixed by the offeror; 

b) If the offeror does not specify, the offer to enter into a contract takes effect from the date the offeree receives the offer, unless otherwise provided for by relevant laws.

2 . The following cases are considered to have received an offer to enter into a contract:

a) The offer is transferred to the place of residence, if the offeree is an individual; to the head office, if the offeree is an individual. the offeree is a juridical person;

b) The offer is entered into the offeree's official information system;

c) When the offeree learns of the offer to enter into a contract through the another method.

Bộ luật dân sự@391:
Termination of the offer to enter into a contract

The offer to enter into a contract shall terminate in the following cases:

1. The offeree accepts to enter into a contract;

2 . The proposed party does not accept;

3. The time limit for replying to accept;

4. When the notice of change or withdrawal of the offer takes effect;

5. When the notice of cancellation of the offer takes effect;

6. According to the agreement of the offeror and the offeree within the time limit waiting for the offeree's reply.

Bộ luật dân sự@398:
Content of the contract

1. The parties to the contract have the right to agree on the content of the contract.

2. A contract may contain the following contents:

a) Object of the contract;

b) Quantity, quality;

c) Price, payment method;

d) Term, location, method of contract performance;

đ) Rights and obligations of the parties;

e) Liability for breach of contract;

g) Dispute settlement method.

Bộ luật dân sự@402:
Main types of contracts

Contracts include the following main types:

1. A bilateral contract is a contract in which each party has obligations towards the other;

2. A unilateral contract is a contract in which only one party has obligations;

3. A main contract is a contract whose validity does not depend on the sub-contract;

4. A sub-contract is a contract. whose validity depends on the main contract;

5. A contract for the benefit of a third party is a contract in which the contracting parties are obliged to perform their obligations and the third party enjoys benefits from the contract. performance of that obligation;

6. A conditional contract is a contract whose performance is subject to the arising, changing or termination of a certain event.

Bộ luật dân sự@420:
Perform the contract when circumstances change substantially

1. Circumstances change substantially when the following conditions are met:

a) Change of circumstances due to customer causes events occurring after the conclusion of the contract;

b) At the time of entering into the contract, the parties could not have foreseen the change in circumstances;

c) The circumstances changed so much that if as the parties know in advance, the contract has not been concluded or is concluded but with completely different content;

d) The continuation of the contract performance without changing the contract content will cause damage to the contract. serious harm to a party;

đ) The party with affected interests has applied all necessary measures in its ability to be able, in accordance with the nature of the contract, but cannot prevent or minimize the degree of influence on the interests.

2. In the event of a fundamental change in circumstances, the party with interests affected has the right to request the other party to renegotiate the contract within a reasonable period.

3. Where the parties cannot agree on the modification of the contract within a reasonable time, one of the parties may request the Court:

a) Termination of the contract at a definite time ;

b) Amendment of the contract to balance the legitimate rights and interests of the parties due to a fundamental change in circumstances.

The court may decide to amend the contract only in case of termination the contract would cause more damage than the costs of performing the contract if modified.

4. In the course of negotiation, amendment and termination of the contract, the Court settles the case, the parties must continue to perform their obligations under the contract, unless otherwise agreed.

Subsection 3. 

MODIFY, TERMINATE THE CONTRACT

Bộ luật dân sự@422:
Terminate the contract

The contract is terminated in the following cases:

1. The contract has been completed;

2. As agreed by the parties;

3 The individual entering into the contract dies, the legal entity entering into the contract ceases to exist, but the contract must be performed by that individual or legal entity;

4. The contract is annulled, unilaterally terminated performance;

5. The contract cannot be performed because the subject matter of the contract no longer exists;

6. The contract is terminated according to the provisions of Article 420 of this Code;

7. other cases prescribed by law.

Bộ luật dân sự@437:
Liability due to incorrect delivery of property

1. In case the seller delivers the property in more quantity than agreed upon, the buyer has the right to receive or not to receive the excess; if received, they must pay for the excess at the price agreed upon in the contract, unless otherwise agreed.

2. In case the seller delivers less than the agreed quantity, the buyer has one of the following rights:

a) Receive the delivered portion and set a time limit for the seller to communicate the missing portion;

b) Receive the delivered portion and claim damages;

c) Cancel the contract and demand compensation for damages if the breach prevents the buyer from achieving the purpose of concluding the contract.

Bộ luật dân sự@439:
Liability to deliver property of wrong type

In case the property is delivered of wrong type, the buyer has one of the following rights:

1. Receive and pay according to the price set by the buyer. The parties agree;

2. Request the delivery of property of the right type and compensation for damage;

3. Cancel the contract and demand compensation for damage if the delivery of the wrong type causes the party to fail. The purchaser fails to achieve the purpose of entering into the contract.

In case the property includes many types but the seller fails to deliver in accordance with the agreement for one or several types, the buyer may cancel the relevant part of the contract. to that type of property and claim damages.

Bộ luật dân sự@505:
Content of cooperation contract

Cooperation contract has the following main contents:

1. Purpose, term of cooperation;

2. Full name, location residence of the individual; name, headquarters of the legal entity;

3. Contribution property, if any;

4. Labor contribution, if any;

5. Method of distribution distribution of profits and profits;

6. Rights and obligations of cooperative members;

7. Rights and obligations of representatives, if any;

8. Conditions for participation and withdrawal from the member's cooperation contract, if any;

9. Conditions for termination of cooperation.

Bộ luật dân sự@512:
Terminate the cooperation contract

1. The cooperation contract terminates in the following cases:

a) According to the agreement of the cooperative members;

b) Expiry term stated in the cooperation contract;

c) The purpose of cooperation has been achieved;

d) According to the decision of the competent state agency;

đ) Other cases as prescribed by the law. This Code and other relevant laws.

2. Upon termination of the cooperation contract, the debts arising from the contract must be paid; if the common property is not enough to repay the debt, the property must be taken. of the cooperative members for payment as prescribed in Article 509 of this Code.

In case the debts have been fully paid but the common property still remains, they shall be divided among the cooperative members according to the provisions of Article 509 of this Code. in proportion to each person's contribution, unless otherwise agreed.

Bộ luật dân sự@525:
Transporter's rights

1. To require the passenger to pay the full freight for the carriage of the passenger, the charge for the carriage of the carry-on baggage in excess of the prescribed amount.

2. Refusal. carry passengers in the following cases:

a) The passenger fails to comply with the carrier's regulations or commits acts of disturbing public order, obstructing the carrier's work, threatening the other people's life, health, property or other unsafe acts during the journey; in this case, the passenger is not entitled to return the freight and must be fined for violation, if the regulations of carriage regulated transportation;

b) Due to the passenger's health condition it is clear to the carrier that the carriage will endanger the passenger itself or others in the journey;

c) To prevent the spread of disease.

Bộ luật dân sự@578:
Terminate the execution of work without authorization

Performance of work without authorization terminates in the following cases:

1. At the request of the person whose work is performed perform;

2. The person whose work is performed, the successor or representative of the person whose work is performed receives the work;

3. The person performing the work is not authorized may continue to perform the work as prescribed in Clause 5, Article 575 of this Code;

4. The person performing the work without authorization dies, if it is an individual, or ceases to exist, if it is a legal entity .

Bộ luật dân sự@589:
Damage to Property Infringed

Damage to Property Infringing includes:

1. Property lost, destroyed or damaged;

2. Benefits associated with the use and exploitation of lost or reduced property;

3. Reasonable costs to prevent, limit and remedy the damage;

4. Other damage caused by rules.

Bộ luật dân sự@590:
Damage caused by infringing health

1. Damage caused by infringing health includes:

a) Reasonable expenses for medical treatment, fostering and rehabilitation and lost or impaired functions of the aggrieved person;

b) The actual lost or reduced income of the aggrieved person; if the aggrieved person's real income is unstable and If it cannot be determined, the average income of workers of the same type shall apply;

c) Reasonable expenses and the actual lost income of caregivers of the aggrieved person during the treatment period; if the aggrieved person loses his ability to work and needs someone to take care of him regularly, the damage includes reasonable expenses for taking care of the aggrieved person;

d) Other damages prescribed by law .

2. The person responsible for compensation in case the health of another person is violated must pay compensation for damage as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article and another sum of money to make up for the mental loss that The level of compensation to compensate for mental loss shall be agreed upon by the parties; if no agreement can be reached, the maximum level for a person whose health is infringed shall not exceed fifty times the base salary prescribed by the State.

Bộ luật dân sự@591:
Damage to life is violated

1. Damage to life is violated includes:

a) Damage to health is infringed according to the provisions of Article 590 of the Ministry this law;

b) Reasonable expenses for burial;

c) Alimony for those for whom the aggrieved person is obligated to support;

d) Other damages prescribed by law determined.

2. The person responsible for compensation in case another person's life is infringed must pay compensation for damage as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article and another sum of money to compensate for the mental loss. for the next of kin in the first line of heirs of the aggrieved person, without these persons, the person whom the aggrieved person has directly raised, the person who has directly raised the aggrieved person is entitled to a sum of money. The level of compensation to compensate for mental loss shall be agreed upon by the parties; if no agreement is reached, the maximum level for a person whose life is infringed shall not exceed one hundred times the basic salary prescribed by the State. .

Bộ luật dân sự@592:
Damage due to infringing upon honor, dignity, or reputation

1. Damage caused by infringing upon honor, dignity or reputation includes:

a) Reasonable expenses to limit or remedy damage;

b) Actual lost or reduced income;

c) Other damage prescribed by law.

2. Person responsible for compensation in In cases where the honor, dignity and reputation of another person is infringed, compensation must be paid for damage as prescribed in Clause 1 of this Article and another sum of money to compensate for the mental loss suffered by that person. usually compensate for mental loss as agreed by the parties; if no agreement is reached, the maximum level for a person whose honor, dignity or reputation has been infringed shall not exceed ten times the basic salary prescribed by the State. determined.

Bộ luật dân sự@617:
Obligations of an estate administrator

1. An estate administrator specified in Clauses 1 and 3, Article 616 of this Code has the following obligations:

a) To make a name property items; recover property belonging to the deceased's estate that other people are possessing, unless otherwise provided for by law;

b) Preserve the estate; not sell, exchange or give as gifts. , pledge, mortgage or otherwise dispose of property, without the written consent of the heirs;

c) Notify the heirs of the status of the estate;

d) Compensate for damage if he/she violates his/her obligations and causes damage;

đ) Returns the estate at the request of the heir.

2. The person who is possessing, using, managing an estate specified in Clause 2, Article 616 of this Code has the following obligations:

a) To preserve the estate; not to sell, exchange, donate, pledge, mortgage or dispose of the property by in other forms;

b) Notice of the estate to the heirs;

c) Compensation for damage if breaching one's obligations causes damage;

d) Handing over the estate as agreed in the contract with the estate leaver or at the request of the heir.

Bộ luật dân sự@618:
Rights of the administrator of the estate

1. An estate administrator specified in Clauses 1 and 3, Article 616 of this Code has the following rights:

a) To represent the heirs in relation to a third person related to the inheritance;

b) To be entitled to remuneration according to the agreement with the heirs;

c) To be paid the cost of preserving the estate .

2. The person who is possessing, using and managing the estate specified in Clause 2, Article 616 of this Code has the following rights:

a) To continue using the estate as agreed upon in the contract. contract with the person leaving the estate or with the consent of the heirs;

b) To receive remuneration as agreed with the heirs;

c) To be paid the cost of preserving the estate. estate.

