Luật Trọng tài thương mại@7:
Determining a Court having jurisdiction over arbitration

1. In case the parties have agreed to select a specific Court, the competent Court is the Court chosen by the parties. choice.

2. In case the parties do not have an agreement to choose a Court, the jurisdiction of the Court is determined as follows:

a) Regarding the appointment of an Arbitrator to establish a Council For ad hoc arbitration, the competent court is the court of the place of residence of the defendant if the defendant is an individual or the place where the defendant's office is located if the defendant is an organization. Jurisdiction is the Court of the place where one of the defendants resides or is headquartered.

In case the defendant has a place of residence or headquarters in a foreign country, the competent court is the Court of the place of residence. or where the plaintiff's office is located;

b) For the change of arbitrator of the ad hoc arbitration council, the competent court is the court where the arbitration council settles the dispute;

c) For a request for settlement of a complaint against an arbitral tribunal's decision on the invalidity of the arbitration agreement, the unenforceable arbitration agreement, and the jurisdiction of the arbitration council, the competent court shall be: The court where the arbitral tribunal makes the decision;

d) For a request for the Court to collect evidence, the competent court is the Court where the evidence needs to be collected;

đ) If the Court requests the Court to apply provisional urgent measures, the competent Court is the Court where the provisional urgent measures need to be applied;

e) For the summoning of witnesses, the Court shall Competent Court is the Court where the witness resides;

g) For a request to cancel an arbitral award or register an ad hoc arbitration award, the competent court is the court where the arbitral tribunal is located. the arbitrator has made the arbitral award.

3. The court with jurisdiction over arbitration activities specified in Clauses 1 and 2 of this Article is the People's Court of a province or centrally run city.

Luật Trọng tài thương mại@12:
Submission of notice and order of delivery of notice

Unless otherwise agreed by the parties or not otherwise provided by the Arbitration Center's rules, the manner and order in which notice shall be sent Arbitration proceedings are prescribed as follows:

1. Each party's explanations, transaction letters and other documents must be sent to the Arbitration Center or the Arbitral Tribunal in a number of copies sufficient for each party. Each member of the arbitration council has one copy, the other party has one copy and one copy is kept at the arbitration center;

2. Notices and documents sent by the arbitration center or the arbitration council to the parties are sent to the addresses of the parties or to their representatives at the correct address notified by the parties;

3. Notices and documents may be sent by the Arbitration Center or the Arbitral Tribunal by method of direct delivery, registered mail, regular mail, fax, telex, telegram, email or by any other method that records this delivery;

4. Notices and documents issued by the Arbitration Center or the Arbitral Tribunal shall be deemed to have received it on the date on which the parties or their representatives have received it or shall be deemed to have received it if the notice or document was sent in accordance with the provisions of paragraph 2 of Article 2. this;

5. The time limit for receiving notices and documents is counted from the day following the day when it is considered to have received notices and documents. If the following day is a holiday or a holiday as prescribed by the country or territory where the notice or document has been received, this time limit starts from the next first working day. If the last day of this time limit is a holiday or holiday as prescribed by the country or territory where the notice or document is received, the expiry date will be the end of the next first working day.

