Luật Trọng tài thương mại@20:
Standards for Arbitrators

1. Persons who fully meet the following criteria can act as Arbitrators:

a) Having full civil act capacity as prescribed by the Ministry civil law;

b) Having a university degree and having worked in the field for 5 years or more;

c) In special cases, experts have high professional qualifications and have a lot of practical experience, although not meeting the requirements mentioned in point b of this clause, may also be selected as arbitrators.

2. Persons who fully meet the criteria specified in Clause 1 of this Article but falling into one of the following cases may not act as arbitrators:

a) Persons currently serving as judges, procurators, investigators, enforcers, civil servants of the People's Courts, procuracies People, investigation agencies, judgment enforcement agencies;

b) Persons who are currently the accused, defendants, people who are serving criminal sentences or have completed serving sentences but have not yet had their criminal records cleared.

3. The arbitration center may impose additional standards higher than those specified in Clause 1 of this Article for its arbitrators.

