Luật Trọng tài thương mại@49:
Authority of the arbitral tribunal to apply interim urgent measures

1. At the request of one of the parties, the arbitral tribunal may apply one or several urgent measures. provisional to the disputing parties.

2. Temporary emergency measures include:

a) Prohibition of altering the status of the property in dispute;

b) Prohibition or compulsion of any which disputing party takes one or more certain acts to prevent acts from adversely affecting the arbitral proceedings;

c) Distraint the property in dispute;

d) Request to preserve, store, sell or dispose of any property of one or the disputing parties;

đ) Interim request for payment between the parties;

e) Prohibition of transfer property rights over the disputed property.

3. During the course of dispute settlement, if one of the parties has requested the Court to apply one or more provisional urgent measures specified in Clause 2 of this Article, but then there is a request to the arbitral tribunal to apply provisional urgent measures, the arbitral tribunal must refuse.

4. Before applying provisional urgent measures, the arbitral tribunal has the right to force the requesting party to apply provisional urgent measures to perform financial security obligations.

5. If the arbitral tribunal applies a different provisional emergency measure or exceeds the request of the requesting party for the application of provisional urgent measures, causing damage to the requesting party, the defendant or a third person, the defendant damages have the right to initiate a lawsuit to the Court to request compensation according to the provisions of the civil procedure law.

