Attached to the application for provisional urgent measures, the party request to provide the Arbitral Tribunal with evidence to substantiate the need to apply such urgent provisional measure.

3. At the discretion of the arbitral tribunal, the party requesting the application of the interim measure. provisional emergency measures must send a sum of money, precious metals, gems or valuable papers fixed by the arbitral tribunal in proportion to the value of damage that may arise as a result of the application of the provisional emergency measure. rightly caused to protect the interests of the party against whom the provisional emergency measure is requested. Money, precious metals, gems or valuable papers are deposited into an escrow account at a bank decided by the arbitration panel.

4. Within 03 working days from the date of receipt of the application, immediately after the requesting party has applied the security measures specified in Clause 3 of this Article, the arbitration council shall consider and issue a decision to apply urgent measures. temporary. In case of refusal to accept the request, the arbitral tribunal shall notify in writing and clearly state the reasons therefor to the requesting party.

