Luật Trọng tài thương mại@59:
Dispute Settlement Suspension

1. Dispute settlement shall be suspended in the following cases:

a) Plaintiff or defendant is a deceased individual whose rights and obligations are their services cannot be inherited;

b) The plaintiff or the defendant is an agency or organization that has terminated its operation, gone bankrupt, dissolved, consolidated, merged, divided, split or transformed its form. Form of organization without any agency or organization taking over the rights and obligations of such agency or organization;

c) The plaintiff withdraws the lawsuit petition or is considered to have withdrawn the lawsuit petition as prescribed in Clause 2 of this Article. Clause 1, Article 56 of this Law, unless the respondent requests to continue settling the dispute;

d) The parties agree to terminate the dispute settlement;

đ) The court has decided the case. The dispute is not within the jurisdiction of the arbitral tribunal, there is no arbitration agreement, the arbitration agreement is invalid, or the arbitration agreement cannot be performed as prescribed in Clause 6, Article 44 of this Law.

2. The arbitral tribunal shall issue a decision to terminate the dispute settlement. In case the arbitration council has not been established, the chairman of the arbitration center shall issue a decision to suspend the dispute settlement.

3. When there is a decision to suspend the settlement of a dispute, the parties are not entitled to initiate a lawsuit to request the Arbitrator to re-settle the dispute if the initiation of the following dispute is not different from the previous dispute about the plaintiff, the defendant and the disputed legal relationship, except for the cases specified at Points c and dd, Clause 1 of this Article.

