Conditions for establishing a school and conditions for being permitted to conduct educational activities

1. A school shall be established when there is a project to establish a school consistent with the socio-economic development planning and planning the network of educational institutions in accordance with the Law on Planning.

The school establishment scheme clearly defines the educational objectives, tasks, programs and contents; land, facilities, equipment equipment, proposed location of school construction, organizational structure, resources and finance; strategic direction of school construction and development.

2. Schools are allowed to conduct educational activities when they meet enough requirements. the following conditions: 

a) Having land, facilities and equipment to meet the requirements of educational activities; The school construction site must ensure an educational and safe environment for learners and students. teachers and employees;

b) Having educational programs and teaching and learning materials according to regulations suitable to each level of education and training level; having a team of qualified teachers and administrators standards, sufficient quantity, uniformity in structure to ensure the implementation of the educational program and the organization of educational activities;

c) Having sufficient financial resources as prescribed to ensure maintenance and develop educational activities;

d) Having regulations on organization and operation of the school.

3. Within the prescribed time limit, if the school fully meets the conditions specified in Clause 2 of this Article, it shall be permitted to conduct educational activities by a competent state agency; upon the expiry of the prescribed time limit, if the conditions specified in Clause 2 of this Article are not satisfied, the establishment decision or the decision on approval for establishment shall be revoked.

Luật Giáo dục@50:
Suspending educational activities

1. The school shall be suspended from educational activities in the following cases:

a) There is a fraudulent act to obtain permission for educational activities; 

b) Failure to meet one of the conditions specified in Clause 2, Article 49 of this Law;

c) The person authorizing educational activities is not authorized;

d) Failure to carry out the activity educational activities within the prescribed time limit from the date of permission to conduct educational activities;

đ) Violating the provisions of the law on education shall be administratively sanctioned to the extent that it must be suspended;

e) Other cases as prescribed by law.

2. A decision to suspend educational activities for a school must clearly specify the reason for the suspension, the duration of the suspension, and measures to ensure rights and interests. benefits of teachers, educational administrators, learners, and employees in the school and must be publicly announced on the mass media.

3. During the suspension period, if the cause is leading to the suspension is remedied, the person competent to decide on the suspension shall issue a decision to allow the school to resume educational operations.

